                "field_htb_introduction": {
                    "en": [
                        {
                            "format": "filtered_html", 
                            "safe_value": "<p>Environmental Rights defenders depend on evidence gathered from sites of ecological and community violations to advocate for favourable public opinion, policy change and government action against these offences. As a result, the security and integrity of evidence is of utmost importance.</p>\n\n<p>Evidence such as interviews, photos, videos and documents stored in computers, phones and other devices can be compromised, stolen or destroyed by adversaries who want to disrupt the work and destroy the credibility of ERDs, if such evidence remains unsecured. Inside informants can also be exposed and action taken against them.</p>\n", 
                            "value": "Environmental Rights defenders depend on evidence gathered from sites of ecological and community violations to advocate for favourable public opinion, policy change and government action against these offences. As a result, the security and integrity of evidence is of utmost importance.\r\n\r\nEvidence such as interviews, photos, videos and documents stored in computers, phones and other devices can be compromised, stolen or destroyed by adversaries who want to disrupt the work and destroy the credibility of ERDs, if such evidence remains unsecured. Inside informants can also be exposed and action taken against them.\r\n"
                        }
                    ]
